{
  "texts": [
    "The final recognition is done by averaging the resulting score vectors.",
    "Multi-stream CNN utilizes a similar approach but uses multiple different networks trained for different image sizes and aspect ratios.",
    "The best plankton recognition accuracy was obtained using a multi-stream network combining two models with different input aspect ratios and patch cropping.",
    "Most plankton datasets have significant variation in image sizes and aspect ratios.",
    "Common CNN-based image classifiers require that the input images have a constant size."
  ]
}